AB  - In a simple two-factor, one commodity model in which foreign labor can be hired at low foreign wage rates and technology is common to both countries, optimal strategy at home involves hiring almost all factors abroad at their autarky prices — a ‘buy-out’ strategy. This paper shows that when technologies differ, partial or, times, complete buy-out of factors from the technologically superior country may still be optimal. Alternatively, a partial buy-out may be appropriate when there exists a third internationally immobile productive factor.
