AB  - We examine trade restrictions such as quantity and quality limitations on imports in an oligopolistic industry consisting of foreign and domestic firms. We find that the effects of trade policy hinge on the location of the quality produced by the firms in the quality spectrum. A quota leads to positive protection while minimum quality standards leads to negative protection. Furthermore, minimum standards lower national welfare and a quota has an ambiguous effect on welfare.
